de.unisiegen.tpml.core.expressions
Interface PrettyPrintPriorities

All Known Implementing Classes:
And, Application, ArithmeticOperator, Assign, BinaryCons, BinaryOperator, BooleanConstant, Condition, Condition1, Constant, CurriedLet, CurriedLetRec, Deref, EmptyList, Exn, Expression, Fst, Hd, Identifier, InfixOperation, IntegerConstant, IsEmpty, Lambda, Let, LetRec, List, Location, MultiLambda, MultiLet, Not, Or, Projection, Recursion, Ref, RelationalOperator, Sequence, Snd, Tl, Tuple, UnaryCons, UnaryListOperator, UnaryOperator, UnitConstant, Value, While
interface PrettyPrintPriorities

This interface includes the pretty print priorities, according to the priority grammar, for the various expressions. It is implemented by the Expression class, so one can easily use the constants in this interface without having to explicitly use this interface each time.

Version:
$Rev: 343 $
Author:
Benedikt Meurer
See Also:
Expression, PrettyStringBuilder
